Recommendations:
We recommended the following:
The project and program proponents to submit proposals to the Municipal Development Council that are specific, measurable, attainable, realistic, and time-bound;
The members of the Municipal Development Council to (a) establish parameters to be used in the appraisal and prioritization of programs and projects; and, (b) maintain an effective line of communication with the proponents and the implementing offices to ensure that the planned programs and projects are implemented;
The implementing offices to strictly observe the timelines set and religiously coordinate with the Municipal Development Council in the execution of planned activities; and,
The LCE to (a) closely monitor the implementation of the projects; and, (b) devise a mechanism by which the status of project implementation is reflected as a parameter in measuring the individual performance of the implementing offices and employees.

