We recommended that the Local  Chief Executive will direct the General Services Office, in coordination with the Accounting Office, to:
1. Create an Inventory Committee that will be responsible  for  the  conduct of physical count;

2. Conduct the  annual  physical  count  of  all  the  property,  plant  and equipment owned by  the  Municipality  to  establish  the  existence  and correct the balances of PPE accounts;

3. Prepare promptly the Report on the Physical Count of PPE;

4. Create an Appraisal Committee  to  appraise  all  properties  which  cost cannot be reliably determined due to unavailability of financial  records. Require the committee  to  prepare  Appraisal  Report  and  submit  it  to Commission on Audit for Technical Review and Inspection; and

